text: Telford is an unincorporated community in Lincoln County, in the U.S. state of Washington. ==History== A post office called Telford was established in 1909, and remained in operation until 1917. The community was named after M. A. Telford, a local cattleman. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Lincoln County, Washington Category:Unincorporated communities in Washington (state)
title: Telford, Washington
